Anavitarte of the 31st and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Denney H. Rogers; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers has faithfully served as mayor of Ephesus, Georgia, for 35
3 years since being elected when his father, Lonnie L. Rogers, the first mayor, retired; he has
4 maintained that post in each election without opposition; and
5 WHEREAS, the Rogers Family has left a long and indelible impact in Ephesus; along with
6 their political history, the family also owned and operated a sawmilling and lumber business
7 named L. L. Rogers and Son; and
8 WHEREAS, Denney lives in the house that his grandfather, Frank Rogers, built in 1923; and
9 WHEREAS, the house recently made history when it was named a Georgia Centennial Farm,
10 as it has been farmed in the same place by the same family for more than 100 years; and
11 WHEREAS, as mayor, Denney has improved his community by building one of the most
12 active libraries in the West Georgia Library System, a city hall that serves the more than 400
13 citizens of Ephesus, and a new fire station that serves the surrounding area; and
