14 WHEREAS, he has led his community to pave roads, build ball fields, and construct an event
15 barn as well as a community center to serve the families of Ephesus and the surrounding
16 area; and
17 WHEREAS, he was instrumental in developing water systems whose lines extend far out of
18 his community in several directions, has added four wells to that system, paid in full for the
19 system, and has done so while keeping his town debt-free; and
20 WHEREAS, he continues to serve his community in developing new projects such as the
21 proposed Veteran's Park, which is in the beginning stages; and
22 WHEREAS, Denney serves his city, county, and state in many other ways including, but not
23 limited to, serving on the West Georgia Regional Library Board for many years, in the local
24 Lions Club, on the Soil and Water Board, with the Rolling Hills Resource Conservation and
25 Development Council with the National Resources Convention Service, as well as serving
26 on the Agribusiness Council Board of Directors and chairing a Sacred Harp singing group
27 that meets annually in the city of Ephesus; and
28 WHEREAS, he is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
29 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
30 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
31 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
33 recognize and commend Denney H. Rogers for his 35 years of service to Ephesus, Georgia,
34 and the surrounding area.
